        "created_at": "2023-10-30T20:35:01.096Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I pulled a '10 Fourrier - Gevrey Chambertin - VV out of my cellar for the first time and noticed it had a wax cap.<br>\nI know the Leroys have wax capsules, do any other producers ?<br>\nWhat are the supposed advantages ?</p>\n<p>btw, the nose on this '10 Fourrier - GC - VV is out of this world.  The wine can use more time, but no crime in opening up one now, and blows away most premier crus.</p>",
