        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/josh_najjar/{size}/1188_2.png",
        "created_at": "2023-10-30T22:52:11.542Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Found this post from 14 years ago.</p>\n<p>Jean Marie goes to quite a degree of trouble with the using of wax. I was amazed to learn that on a good day, they can only wax seal 1000 bottles. That makes for a lot of manual work! Jean Marie is a very thoughtful and scientifically minded guy, he\u2019s convinced that the wax seal aids the wine\u2019s evolution.</p>\n<p>Any idea how the wax aids in a wine\u2019s evolution ?<br>\nSlowing the transference of air through the cork ?</p>",
        "post_number": 4,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 11,
        "updated_at": "2023-10-30T22:52:11.542Z",
